Social Services in the Community       Social Services in the Community      Through their Field Placements, Jane Addams MSW students provide needed social services at a variety of agencies, hospitals, schools and other organizations throughout the Chicago metropolitan area.       Services Provided in the 2018-19 Academic Year        291   Sites in the Chicago area where our students provided services         239,940   Hours of social services provided by our students           Types of Service Provided   For its Field Placements, the college maintains relationships with over 300 agencies, hospitals, schools and other organizations throughout the Chicago metropolitan area. These organizations provide services in areas such as:   Addictions/Physical dependence  Administration  Aging/Gerontological social work  Child welfare  Community development/Planning  Community mental health, or mental health  Corrections/Criminal Justice  Developmental disabilities  Displaced persons/Homeless  Domestic violence, or violence  Family services  Health/Integrative health and mental health  Immigrant/Refugee work  LGBTQ services  Military social work  Policy practice  Program evaluation  PTSD/Veterans  Public assistance/Public welfare  Rehabilitation  School social work       Learn More About  Field Placements          Community Impact    Back to main content           Jane Addams Center for Social Policy and Research     Center Leadership & Staff    Research & Sponsored Projects    Service Projects    Public Forums & Events    Center Publications    Journal of Offender Rehabilitation    Consultation & Technical Assistance      Midwest Latino Health Research, Training and Policy Center    Training Institute for School Social Work Professionals    Social Services in the Community    Research & Sponsored Projects              Jane Addams College of Social Work  UI Health                        UIC's seven health sciences colleges and health care delivery enterprise.       Footer Menu 